          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " the  method  of  Penfold  and Leiss was used to",
                " extract the total neutron  cross  section  from  the",
                " yield curves."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photoneutron yields from Li,  N14,  and Ar40 have",
                " been   measured   as   a  function  of  the  maximum",
                " bremsstrahlung    energy    from    threshold     to",
                " approximately 50 MeV.  Sigma t = (g,n) + sigma(g,pn)",
                " +  2sigma(g,2n) +....   results  are  compared  with",
                " previous  findings  of other laboratories.  No gross",
                " structure was detected in the lithium cross  section",
                " in  the  giant  resonance region.  The data indicate",
                " that lithium has a high-energy  tail  on  the  cross",
                " section of considerable magnitude."
              ]
            }
          ],
